# WHAT IT IS
#   Corvid is "the programming language that checks your AI before it
#   runs" — Micrurus AI's effect-typed language for LLM-orchestrating
#   programs.  Every Corvid function carries a typed effect profile
#   (model + tool calls + costs + privacy + provenance) checked at
#   compile time, and the compiler emits artifacts for multiple
#   targets:  Python (default `target/py/`), native AOT
#   (`target/bin/`), WebAssembly (`target/wasm/` with JS loader + TS
#   types), cdylib (with optional signed ABI descriptor for host
#   compliance verification), staticlib, and an HTTP server.  The
#   driver bundles a REPL, an LSP server, a deterministic trace
#   replay engine, a routing-report aggregator, and a Pareto-frontier
#   prompt-cost analyzer.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from crates/corvid-cli/src/main.rs
#                       module-doc subcommand index + cli/root.rs
#                       clap-derive Cli + Command enum)
#   corvid <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Project / build commands:
#     new <NAME>                    Scaffold a new Corvid project
#     check <FILE>                  Type-check a source file
#     build [<FILE>]                Compile (default file: src/main.cor)
#       --target <TGT>                Output target [default: python;
#                                     also: native, server, wasm,
#                                     cdylib, staticlib]
#       --with-tools-lib <PATH>       Compiled #[tool] staticlib to
#                                     link against
#       --header                      Emit companion C header
#       --abi-descriptor              Emit ABI descriptor (cdylib only)
#       --all-artifacts               Emit every companion artifact
#       --sign <KEY_PATH>             Sign cdylib ABI descriptor with
#                                     ed25519 key (or
#                                     $CORVID_SIGNING_KEY env var)
#       --key-id <ID>                 DSSE `keyid` field
#                                     [default: "build-key"]
#     run [<FILE>]                  Compile + invoke target runtime
#     repl                          Start the interactive REPL
#
#   Testing & verification:
#     test [<FILE> | <WHAT>]        Run tests / verification suites
#                                   (dimensions, spec, rewrites,
#                                    adversarial)
#     verify                        Cross-tier effect-profile
#                                   verification
#     effect-diff                   Diff composed effect profiles
#                                   between two revisions
#
#   Package management:
#     add                           Add a dependency to Corvid.lock
#     remove                        Remove a dependency
#     update                        Refresh a dependency through its
#                                   registry
#     add-dimension                 Install a dimension from the
#                                   effect registry
#
#   Analysis / observability:
#     routing-report                Aggregate dispatch traces into
#                                   routing guidance
#     cost-frontier                 Compute prompt cost / quality
#                                   Pareto frontier
#     tour                          Open runnable demos
#     import-summary                Inspect imported module semantic
#                                   contracts
#     eval --swap-model <ID> <TRACE>
#                                   Retrospective model-migration
#                                   analysis
#     replay <TRACE>                Re-execute a recorded trace
#                                   deterministically
#       --model <ID>                  Differential replay against a
#                                     different model
#
#   ABI / trace / receipt commands:
#     abi dump <LIB>                Inspect the embedded ABI /
#                                   capability catalog
#     trace list                    List traces under target/trace/
#     trace show <ID>               Print recorded trace as JSON
#     trace dag <ID>                Render provenance DAG as
#                                   Graphviz DOT
#     claim --explain <LIB>         Explain the guarantees claimed
#                                   by a cdylib
#
#   Plus per-group subcommand trees:
#     app, approvals, approver, auth (with keys subcommand),
#     bench, bind, bundle, capsule, connectors (with oauth
#     subcommand), contract, deploy, doctor, jobs (explain),
#     lineage, migrate, observe, ops, package, receipt,
#     release, review-queue, serve, upgrade, audit.
#
#   Standard clap auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                    Show help
#     -V, --version                 Show version
